The Limpopo Health Department says that it is worried that Pastor Lethebo Rabalago's actions could possibly be linked to mental illness. JOHANNESBURG The Limpopo Health Department says it s trying to arrange for the pastor who used Doom insecticide on churchgoers to undergo psychiatric evaluation.Pastor Lethebo Rabalago has been photographed spraying Doom in the faces of people attending his services. Rabalago claims God instructed him to do so. However, the department says it s worried that his actions could possibly be linked to mental illness.Limpopo Health MEC Phophi Ramathuba says: We strongly believe from the symptoms, and the behavioural patterns, that we might be dealing with a person whose mental state is not sound. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)